---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Request Listing Removal | Sydney Anxiety Psychology Directory"
  description="Request removal of your profile from the Sydney Anxiety Psychology directory. Removals are processed within 24 hours, no questions asked."
>
  <div class="main-content">
    <div class="container">

      <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        <a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo; <a href="/directory/">Directory</a> &rsaquo; Request Removal
      </p>

      <h1>Request Profile Removal</h1>

      <div class="info-box" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <p>
          <strong>We remove profiles within 24 hours of a valid request, no questions asked.</strong>
          If your name appears on this directory and you would prefer it removed, send us an email
          and we will action it the same business day.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>How to request removal</h2>
      <p>
        Send an email to
        <a href="mailto:team@sydneyanxietypsychology.com.au">team@sydneyanxietypsychology.com.au</a>
        with the subject line "Profile removal request" and include:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Your full name as it appears on the directory</li>
        <li>The URL of your profile page (e.g. <code style="font-size: 0.9rem; background: var(--color-surface-alt); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px;">https://sydneyanxietypsychology.com.au/directory/your-name-suburb/</code>)</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        We do not require a reason and will not ask for one. Removal is free and permanent.
        Once removed, the page will return a 404 and the URL will be submitted to Google for
        de-indexation within 48 hours.
      </p>

      <h2>Why do profiles exist before practitioners consent?</h2>
      <p>
        This directory pre-builds skeleton profiles using only data from the
        <a href="https://www.ahpra.gov.au/Registration/Registers-of-Practitioners.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AHPRA public register</a>,
        which is freely and publicly accessible government data. The profile contains only:
        your full name, registration type, and principal practice suburb. No contact details,
        no clinical claims, no fabricated content.
      </p>
      <p>
        Profiles are labelled "Unclaimed" and include a prominent removal link (this page) on every page.
        This model is used by a number of Australian health directories and is consistent with
        the AHPRA register being publicly accessible data.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you would prefer to claim and enrich your profile rather than remove it, visit
        <a href="/for-psychologists/">the practitioner page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy and data held</h2>
      <p>
        Skeleton profiles contain only AHPRA public register data (name, registration type, suburb).
        We do not hold your contact details, Medicare provider number, or any data not sourced
        from the public register. After removal, all records associated with your profile are deleted.
        See our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
